## 2. AUTHORIZATION — 🚨 CRITICAL FINDINGS

### 🔴 Issue 2.1: Admin Server Actions Have NO Authentication Checks

- **Severity:** **CRITICAL**
- **Issue:** Every admin server action in [content.ts](file:///c:/Users/habib/Downloads/admin-panel-plan-2/app/admin/actions/content.ts) (`saveProgramme`, `removeProgramme`, `saveSettings`, `seedDbAction`, `changeApplicationStatus`, `removeApplication`, `uploadFile`, `deleteApplicationsAction`, etc.) performs **zero** authentication verification. They are marked `'use server'` but never call `getUser()` or check the session.
- **Impact:** **Any unauthenticated user** can invoke these server actions directly via HTTP POST. An attacker can:
  - Modify/delete all programmes, testimonials, blog posts, settings
  - Upload arbitrary files
  - Delete all user applications and submissions
  - Seed/wipe the entire database
  - Change site settings (redirect URLs, privacy policy content)
- **Location:** [content.ts](file:///c:/Users/habib/Downloads/admin-panel-plan-2/app/admin/actions/content.ts) — ALL 20+ exported functions
- **Fix:** Add authentication guard to every admin server action:

```ts
// app/admin/actions/content.ts - Add at top
import { createActionClient } from '@/lib/supabase'

async function requireAdmin() {
  const supabase = await createActionClient()
  const { data: { user } } = await supabase.auth.getUser()
  if (!user) {
    throw new Error('Unauthorized')
  }
  return user
}

// Then in every exported function:
export async function saveProgramme(programme: Programme, originalSlug?: string) {
  await requireAdmin()  // ← ADD THIS
  await store.upsertProgramme(programme, originalSlug)
  refreshAll()
}
```

> [!CAUTION]
> **This is your #1 priority fix.** The middleware only protects page rendering (GET requests to `/admin/*`). Server Actions are callable independently — they are not protected by the route middleware. Every admin action can be invoked by an unauthenticated user today.

### 🟡 Issue 2.2: No Role-Based Access Control

- **Severity:** Medium
- **Issue:** Any authenticated Supabase user (not necessarily an admin) could invoke admin actions. There is no role check — only session existence.
- **Impact:** If Supabase Auth has non-admin users (e.g., if you later add user-facing auth), they would have full admin access.
- **Location:** Entire admin actions layer
- **Fix:** Add a role check or restrict to specific email addresses:
  ```ts
  const ADMIN_EMAILS = ['admin@uptrail.com']
  
  async function requireAdmin() {
    const supabase = await createActionClient()
    const { data: { user } } = await supabase.auth.getUser()
    if (!user || !ADMIN_EMAILS.includes(user.email!)) {
      throw new Error('Unauthorized')
    }
  }
  ```

